    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I'm struck by the similarity between Haqqania madrasa students and the home-schooled children of Christian fundamentalists. Neither group confines its religious fervor to its members, but seeks to change the world around it through both political militancy and personal evangelism. I'm alarmed to see one considered a threat to national security and the other a counterculture curiosity.</p>
        <p>Anne Shaw  Milwaukee</p>
      </block>
